        "question": "What drum kit did Igor Cavalera use on Sepultura's Arise?",
        "answer": "On Sepultura's Arise recorded in 1990 and released in 1991, Igor Cavalera played a Tama Artstar II kit with birch shells. The setup included dual 22x16 inch bass drums, three rack toms in 10, 12, and 13 inch sizes, and a single 16 inch floor tom. This was a significant professional upgrade from the Pearl Export he used on Beneath the Remains, with the Artstar II's birch shells delivering the sharper attack and greater resonance needed for the album's technically demanding material. The Tama Star-Cast mounting system allowed the shells to resonate more freely, contributing to the fuller tom sound audible throughout the album."
